# grafana-server.service — Host-first deployment systemd unit

## Overview

This systemd unit file runs Grafana for the LLM proxy stack monitoring
infrastructure. It uses the host-first model (binary installation, no
containers) and is designed to be deployed as a **user service**.

## User Service (Recommended)

**File location**: `~/.config/systemd/user/grafana-server.service`

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Grafana dashboard server for LLM proxy stack
After=network.target prometheus.service
Wants=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
ExecStart=/home/rgardler/bin/grafana/bin/grafana-server \
  --homepath=/home/rgardler/bin/grafana \
  --config=/home/rgardler/bin/grafana/conf/defaults.ini \
  --packaging=unknown

# Restart policy
Restart=always
RestartSec=5

# Logging
StandardOutput=append:/home/rgardler/.local/state/grafana/logs/grafana.log
StandardError=append:/home/rgardler/.local/state/grafana/logs/grafana.log

# Resource limits
MemoryMax=1G

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
```

### Setup commands (user service)

```bash
# Create directories
mkdir -p ~/.local/share/grafana/data
mkdir -p ~/.local/state/grafana/logs

# Copy provisioning files
cp monitoring/grafana/datasources/datasources.yaml ~/bin/grafana/conf/provisioning/datasources/
cp monitoring/grafana/dashboards/dashboards.yaml ~/bin/grafana/conf/provisioning/dashboards/
cp monitoring/grafana_llama_memory_dashboard.json ~/bin/grafana/conf/provisioning/dashboards/

# Enable and start the service
systemctl --user daemon-reload
systemctl --user enable grafana-server.service
systemctl --user start grafana-server.service

# Check status
systemctl --user status grafana-server.service

# View logs
journalctl --user -u grafana-server.service -f
```

## Verification

```bash
# Check Grafana health
curl http://localhost:3000/api/health

# Open Grafana in browser
# http://localhost:3000
# Default credentials: admin / admin

# Verify Prometheus datasource is configured
curl -u admin:admin http://localhost:3000/api/datasources

# Verify dashboards are loaded
curl -u admin:admin http://localhost:3000/api/search?type=dash-db
```

